decision_conditions:
"	Islington believe that there will be an impact on viability of the proposed changes and want to ensure that the opportunity to secure more affordable housing or S106 contributions is not lost.  The updated viability assessment should be independently assessed or the 1st stage viability review in the S106 should be amended to secure 100% of any surplus for affordable housing rather than 50%; 
"	There are likely to be detailed comments on the viability information submitted and these will follow; 
"	Islington would expect to be a signatory to any deed of variation and object to the use of a Unilateral Undertaking unless we can see and comment on a draft of the Unilateral Undertaking; 
"	Please note that Islington does note that Islington Council does not support the use of Affordable Rent as part of the affordable housing provision.
"	Please note that One Housing are not listed in the approved list of registered providers at Schedule 9 of the S106.
